Yes you can do that

I tried purchasing linens today through the Vassar-RHL platform, but it was closed, i.e they couldn't deliver to Vassar students. I then tried the regular RHL platform and ut worked fine. The only problem I'm having is with the shipping address. Can I indicate my Vassar Mail Box address, and then collect the package at the Central Receiving Dept. ?
Hello everyone. I'm having a little problem, and I've mailed reslife, but they haven't replied
Thank you. Who else will be staying there?
Congrats!
Hello all..Just got assigned to Josselyn House!!!!
Okay. Thanks a lot
I think I'll settle for the prepaid plans then
And most people use macs here but you can use whatever you want
There are prepaid plans like we have in Nigeria but most people have two year contracts during which they pay a monthly fee for the cost of the phone and as well as monthly usage.

My mum is stressing on me taking a lot of clothes, which I'm okay with. I'm coming with the basic stuff I need anyway. In terms of technological gadgets (phones and the rest), what's it like over there and for laptops, windows or mac?

Hmm that's a good question. It depends on you budget. If you plan on buying a lot of things when you get here then it wouldn't be advisable to pack all that stuff. If not the bring along the things you'll need. Also check your ticket to see the baggage allowance and plan accordingly
Daniel named the group Vassaranianz.

So, Anu made mention of a boat, which I guess I'm not really on yet. I'm about to get on and I'm in that stage of packing. I'm worried about over packing and under packing, so please, tips on the what's and the 'what not's'. Thank you all, once againó¾°. And also can I get to know your class years
Thank you Anu, Solomon and Dami
Congrats Daniel!
Welcome Daniel
Anu Oluwa added you to the group.
Also Daniel, feel free to message me or anyone else if you have any questions. Once again congratulations!

Hey guys, I hope your summers are going great! So... finally we have another Nigerian coming to Vassar fresh off the boat! His name is Daniel Elendu and he should be there by August. So please show him some love and get him plugged to the ASU (Daniel, that's the African Students Union). I hope to see you guys soon!
